messages.text: Sergeant Delaney?
Ada? Are you okay?
Yeah.
I thought you were dead.
So I heard.
What do you mean?
Never mind. Is it true?
Is what true?
What I’m seeing on the news.
That my dad caused all of this.
I’m afraid so.
I don’t believe it.
I didn’t want to either. But it’s true.
That’s why he was arrested?
If only your mom had made it…
she could have told you.
Mom?
She knew.
Look, Ada, I promise to explain everything once you’re safe…
But right now, I need to get you here to Houston
and on a transport to a more secure location.
So dad was right.
The bombs didn’t work?
No. We couldn’t get them all.
There are too many infected.
And now it’s dark, and the virus is spreading again…
sweeping through the suburbs of Houston like wildfire.
Gunships are doing their best to slow it down
but it’s too late.
We’re past the tipping point.
No one can stop it now.
So please tell me where you are Ada.
I’ll send a helicopter and a detachment of marines.
Not until I get some answers.
Ada, please!
I know there’s something about me
some reason you need me there…
So either answer my questions
or I disappear.
OK, you win.
What do you want to know?
Why the hell did my mom make something that does this?
First of all, no single person created this.
It takes a team of very intelligent people to design something this complex.
Your mother’s job was to create a vaccine and, eventually, a cure…
but to do that, she had to be in on the design of the virus too.
So there’s a cure?
Everyone even remotely involved with the project was vaccinated.
Me. Your dad. Your mom.
Even you and Christian.
I was never vaccinated.
You were. You just didn’t know it.
Jesus Christ
is everything I’ve ever been told a lie?
Let’s just say that no one at Ft. Hood was what they seemed.
Sorry.
If everyone was vaccinated, how did this happen?
We BELIEVED there was a viable vaccine.
It worked in the lab, but…
Apparently, immunization never occurred in humans.
Apparently?!
The outbreaks at Ft. Hood and in San Antonio proved that.
How could you NOT know that the cure didn’t work?!
The only way to know for certain would have been to expose vaccinated humans to the virus.
Your mother refused to allow that.
Figures. The one thing you idiots did right and it was a mistake.
We made a lot of mistakes.
I still don’t understand why ANYONE would create this.
Because if we can make it
then so can our enemies.
We had to be the first.
And we do it all the time.
So how is that working out for us now?
Poorly.
But trust me, we have worse than this in our arsenal.
I don’t get it, though?
Why create something that turns humans into zombies?
The virus isn’t supposed to turn humans into zombies, exactly.
More like programmable drones.
The idea was to create a virus that debilitated humans in a specific way
which would allow us to re-program them for our own use.
This sounds like ‘Attack of the Clones’ shit to me.
Yeah, sort of.
But it wasn’t even close to being done, yet.
It’s having unpredicted affects.
Making some people really violent
and others just crazy.
Jesus.
So whose idea was it to make this thing?
Originally?
Your dad’s.
And our government was on board from the very beginning?
Few knew about the project.
But enough to get an official go ahead.
I guess they all know now.
That and more.
About a year ago, your dad approached me with an idea…
He wanted to let the finished virus spread through the Middle East
and China
and eventually up into Russia.
What?! Why?!
To eliminate any opposition to U.S. world supremacy.
He wouldn’t.
I know it’s hard to accept.
That my dad wanted to kill half the planet?
Yeah.
If it means anything, he believed he was doing what was best for his country.
And you’re absolutely positive he’s responsible?
Your mother found proof of your dad’s plan to release the virus unsanctioned.
She was about to expose him…
So he had his people cause the outbreaks at both bases.
Doesn’t sound very patriotic to me.
We don’t have all the answers yet, Ada.
I’m sorry.
You should be.
You all should be.
We are.
No one more than me.
So why are you so desperate to find me?
It’s a promise I made your mom.
If something like this happened…
or if your dad found out she knew…
I would get you out and meet her at my cabin.
That’s why she was there yesterday?!
I believe so.
Even after being infected, her instinct was to find you.
Why didn’t you tell me this instead of kidnapping me?
I didn’t kidnap you
I rescued you.
And I was going to tell you when you woke up…
But you shot me. Remember? ☺
Oh yeah. Sorry about that.
It’s okay.
Now please tell me where you are.
Ada?
I’m here in Houston.
And I want to see my dad.
